          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632301720442-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, place your<strong> creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (in its packaging!) in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p><p>Peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and your <strong>garlic</strong>, then finely chop (or grate) both</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass stalk[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut it down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough</strong> <strong>outer layers</strong> and set aside for later, then chop the <strong>soft inner core[s]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632301725676-x200.jpg",
